Reasoning: The paper deals with the maximization of mutual information in a Gaussian interference channel using game theory, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of game theory to design multiuser MIMO systems, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves the study of distributed algorithms, which is a topic in networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the convergence of algorithms, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with the extension of the game to the more general MIMO case, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
